The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 BCCIs yes to four Tests 

St Johns: India will play four Tests in the Caribbean in May-June this year after the Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) agreed on the schedule proposed by the West Indies Cricket Board (WICB), it was announced on Wednesday. 

The BCCI had pressed for three Tests but consented to the WICB request at a meeting in Dubai. 

The WICB is pleased that the BCCI has agreed to maintain the four Test schedule and we in turn have agreed to adjust the one-day International schedule to eliminate back-to-back matches, WICB chief executive Roger Brathwaite said. 

THE ITINERARY 

May 12: Arrival. May 16: Tour match vs WIPA Masters in Jamaica; May 18: 1st ODI in Jamaica; May 20: 2nd ODI in Jamaica; May 23: 3rd ODI in St Kitts; May 26: 4th ODI in Trinidad; May 28: 5th ODI in Trinidad; May 30-31: Tour match in Antigua; June 2-6: 1st Test in Antigua; June 10-14: 2nd Test in St. Lucia; June 22-26: 3rd Test in St. Kitts; June 30-July 4: 4th Test in Jamaica. (PTI) 




